Rggml vendors a CPU-only subset of the GGML tensor library as third-party C
and C++ source, built into a static library (inst/ggml/libggml.a) and
exposed through Rggml's own C-callable API. This file documents what was
vendored, from where, and under what license.

Upstream project
-----------------
GGML: https://github.com/ggml-org/ggml
Copyright (c) Georgi Gerganov and contributors.
License: MIT (see "Verbatim upstream LICENSE text" below).

Immediate vendoring source
---------------------------
The GGML sources here were not copied directly from the ggml-org/ggml
repository. They were copied from an existing CRAN-facing R package,
'ggmlR' (https://github.com/Zabis13/ggmlR by Yuri Baramykov, MIT licensed),
which already vendors GGML with the R-specific adaptations Rggml also
needs (notably the stdio/abort CRAN-compliance shim, see below). ggmlR's
DESCRIPTION records the vendored GGML version as 0.9.5; that version
string and 'ggmlR' as the placeholder commit are compiled in unchanged
(see inst/ggml/Makefile: -DGGML_VERSION, -DGGML_COMMIT) because ggmlR
itself does not preserve the exact upstream ggml-org/ggml commit hash.
Rggml's own C-callable API version (separate from the GGML library
version) is tracked by RGGML_API_VERSION in src/rggml_api.h.

ggmlR itself also splits GGML's monolithic ggml.c and ggml-cpu/ops.cpp
into several smaller translation units compiled together as a single unit
(ggml-core.c/ggml-context.c/ggml-ops-builders.c/ggml-graph.c/ggml-misc.c,
included from ggml-private.c; ggml-cpu/ops-elemwise.cpp/ops-tensor.cpp/
ops-rope-attn.cpp/ops-ssm.cpp/ops-recurrent.cpp/ops-misc.cpp, included
from ggml-cpu/ops-private.cpp). Rggml keeps that split as-is.

What was vendored (CPU backend only)
-------------------------------------
Under inst/ggml/ (built into libggml.a) and inst/include/ (installed
public headers, also used by Rggml.h and by downstream LinkingTo
packages):

  Core tensor/context/graph:
    ggml-private.c (unity include of ggml-core.c, ggml-context.c,
      ggml-ops-builders.c, ggml-graph.c, ggml-misc.c), ggml-alloc.c,
      ggml-impl.h, ggml-common.h, ggml-cpp.h, gguf.h (header only - GGUF
      file I/O itself, gguf.cpp, is NOT vendored; ggml-impl.h merely
      declares two gguf_* helper prototypes that are never called here)
  Backend plumbing:
    ggml-backend.cpp, ggml-backend-reg.cpp, ggml-backend-meta.cpp,
      ggml-backend-impl.h, ggml-threading.cpp, ggml-threading.h
  BLAS backend:
    ggml-blas.cpp (inst/ggml/) and ggml-blas.h (inst/include/) - unlike
      the rest, these were copied directly from ggml-org/ggml (ggmlR is
      CPU-only and does not vendor the BLAS backend). Still MIT. GGML's
      BLAS backend offloads dense F32 mul_mat to a system BLAS; Rggml
      points it at R's own BLAS (see "CBLAS -> Fortran BLAS shim" below).
  Quantization (tensor-level quantize/dequantize):
    ggml-quants-legacy.c, ggml-quants-iq.c, ggml-quants-new.c,
      ggml-quants-validate.c, ggml-quants.h, ggml-quants-helpers.h,
      ggml-quants-new.h
  CPU backend (inst/ggml/ggml-cpu/):
    ggml-cpu.cpp, ggml-cpu-backend.c, ggml-cpu-impl.h, arch-fallback.h,
      common.h, simd-gemm.h, simd-mappings.h, traits.cpp/.h, vec.cpp/.h,
      quants.c/.h (CPU vec-dot/dequant kernels, distinct from the
      tensor-level ggml-quants-*.c files above), repack.cpp/.h,
      binary-ops.cpp/.h, unary-ops.cpp/.h, ops.h, ops-private.cpp (unity
      include of ops-elemwise.cpp, ops-tensor.cpp, ops-rope-attn.cpp,
      ops-ssm.cpp, ops-recurrent.cpp, ops-misc.cpp), amx/amx.h (header
      only; the AMX kernels themselves, amx/amx.cpp and amx/mmq.cpp, are
      NOT vendored - the header's declarations are compiled out unless
      __AMX_INT8__/__AVX512VNNI__ are defined, which this build never
      sets)
  Installed public headers (inst/include/), also used by downstream
  LinkingTo packages via Rggml.h:
    ggml.h, ggml-alloc.h, ggml-backend.h, ggml-cpu.h

Rggml builds the CPU kernels in an architecture-generic (GGML_CPU_GENERIC)
configuration: no SIMD compiler flags, no OpenMP, and none of the
hand-written x86 SIMD kernel files (ggml-cpu/arch/x86/*). GGML's BLAS
backend (GGML_USE_BLAS, ggml-blas.cpp) IS built: dense F32 mul_mat
offloads to R's own BLAS through the shim described below. GGML's GPU and
other backends (CUDA/Metal/SYCL/Vulkan/RPC/CANN/...) are not vendored or
compiled. See README.md for what a future Vulkan backend addition would
need, and for the planned runtime-SIMD-dispatched quantized kernels.

Deliberately NOT vendored (present in ggmlR but out of scope for Rggml):
  - src/ggml-vulkan/ (the entire Vulkan backend and its shader sources)
  - src/onnx/ (ONNX model loading)
  - src/ggml-opt.cpp/.h (the optimizer/autograd training engine)
  - src/gguf.cpp (GGUF file I/O; gguf.h is vendored as a header-only
    dependency of ggml-impl.h, see above)
  - src/ggml-cpu/amx/amx.cpp, amx/mmq.cpp, amx/common.h (AMX kernels)
  - src/ggml-cpu/llamafile/sgemm.cpp (Mozilla Foundation's hand-tuned
    x86 SIMD sgemm; not needed for a portable generic CPU build)
  - src/ggml-cpu/arch/x86/* (hand-written x86 SIMD kernels)
  - src/r_interface*.c, src/r_ggml_io.c (ggmlR's own R-level bindings;
    Rggml's C-callable API and rggml_io.c/rggml_compat.h below are a
    fresh implementation of the same idea, not copies of ggmlR's R
    bindings)

CRAN-compliance I/O shim
--------------------------
inst/ggml/rggml_compat.h and inst/ggml/rggml_io.c are adapted, with only
cosmetic renaming (r_ggml_* -> unchanged internally; file names r_ggml_
compat.h/r_ggml_io.c -> rggml_compat.h/rggml_io.c), from ggmlR's
src/r_ggml_compat.h and src/r_ggml_io.c. They redirect the vendored GGML
code's stdio (printf/fprintf/puts/...) and process-terminating calls
(abort/exit/_Exit) to R-safe equivalents (Rprintf/REprintf/Rf_error), per
CRAN policy (no direct writes to the console, no calls that can terminate
the R session). This mechanism is ggmlR's own original contribution (not
part of upstream GGML) and is MIT licensed along with the rest of ggmlR.

CBLAS -> Fortran BLAS shim
---------------------------
GGML's BLAS backend (ggml-blas.cpp) calls the C CBLAS interface
(cblas_sgemm), which R does not guarantee: R links against a BLAS that
exposes the Fortran interface (sgemm_), not necessarily CBLAS. Rather than
add a system CBLAS dependency, inst/ggml/cblas.h and inst/ggml/rggml_cblas.c
provide a minimal cblas_sgemm() that forwards to Fortran sgemm_ via R's
F77_NAME() convention (the final Rggml.so links $(BLAS_LIBS) $(FLIBS)).
These two files are Rggml's own original code, not derived from GGML or
ggmlR, and are GPL (>= 2) like the rest of Rggml.

Runtime SIMD dispatch (tools/simd/)
------------------------------------
tools/simd/cpu_features.c and cpu_features.h are copied from the R package
'RsimdDispatch' (https://github.com/sounkou-bioinfo/RsimdDispatch, GPL (>= 2),
by the same author as Rggml). They provide runtime CPUID/ISA detection used by
Rggml's SIMD dispatcher. tools/simd/rggml_simd_dispatch.c (the dispatcher) and
tools/simd/vec_dot_q4_K.c (a copy of GGML's ggml_vec_dot_q4_K_q8_K_generic body
from ggml-cpu/quants.c, compiled by configure with per-ISA flags into staged
variants) are Rggml's own code, GPL (>= 2). The vec_dot_q4_K.c body is a
verbatim derivative of GGML (MIT) and is kept in sync with quants.c.

